	Reconcile the records with the Municipal Treasurer.

We recommended, and the management agreed, that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant – Designate to:
	comply with the proper recording procedures in the recognition of mandatory deductions and their remittances;
	make sure that the amount posted in the GL is equal to the amount in the payroll and schedules;
	prepare a subsidiary ledger for mandatory deductions which includes the payroll number, and check number of the amount withheld and remitted; and
	prepare and send confirmation letters to GSIS, Pag-IBIG, and PhilHealth for unremitted amounts in the records of the Municipality.

We recommended, and the management agreed, that the Municipal Mayor:

a.	fill the vacant position in the LDRRM Office to ensure the adequacy of personnel who will prepare, implement and coordinate the DRRM plans and programs to enhance the capacity of the Municipality before, during and after the occurrence of disasters;
.	direct the Municipal Accountant – Designate to prepare the Monthly Report of Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF and submit the same to the COA auditor on or before the 15th day after the end of each month;
	c.	instruct the MDRRMO to incorporate under a separate caption in the LDRRMFIP the list of projects and activities which are to be charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years which were transferred to the Special Trust Fund, and use the prescribed format of the report;
	d.	ensure that all disbursement vouchers are properly approved and supported with the necessary documents; and
	e.	ensure that all reports related to the reporting of the LDRRM Fund are consistent.

