We recommended that the:

Local Chief Executive forms an Inventory Committee and sign a Physical Inventory Plan.

Inventory Committee conducts physical count and prepares and submits the RCPPE;

Municipal Treasurer issues Acknowledgment Receipt of Equipment, attach property stickers and update property cards;

Municipal Accountant – Designate properly computes the depreciation and reconcile with general ledger balances and results of the inventory.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive enforce compliance with the terms and conditions of the loan contract, and direct the Municipal Accountant-Designate to:

Prepare the necessary journal entries to correct the deficiencies;

Inquire with LBP on the loan repayment scheme and conduct a periodic reconciliation of the loan balance with the bank to ensure early detection of unreconciled items;

Maintain and update a subsidiary ledger for the loan to ensure that loan amortizations and all other charges are paid regularly and on time;

Ensure that the Loans Payable–Domestic account is properly disclosed in the Notes to FS in accordance with the guidelines in the IPSAS and other regulatory bodies.

We likewise recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Budget Officer to provide the Audit Team with a copy of the approved Supplemental Budget particularly on the debt repayment of the Loans Payable.

We recommended that the LCE direct the:

Budget Officer to submit documents to substantiate the realignment of the budgeted DF;

Municipal Engineer to regularly conduct an ocular inspection and report the status of the project, copy furnish this Office;

Moving forward, ensure the proper utilization of the 20% DF as prescribed in DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017-1.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the officials concerned to:

Immediately submit the DVs and lacking supporting documents;

Prepare the required adjusting entries;

Reimburse the BGCM Fund used in purchasing prohibited administrative equipment from General Fund;

Ensure the posting of the required reports of the BGCM, and submit copies of the same to the Audit Team;

Reconstruct inventory records pertaining to the procurement of COVID-19 related supplies and materials, and reconcile inventory with the accounting records.

We recommended, and Management agreed to direct the:

a. 	LDRRMO to include all the unexpended prior year balance in its LDRRMIP and use the format specified in Annex A of COA Circular No. 2012-02;

b.	Municipal Accountant – Designate to submit Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization on or before the 15th day after the end of each month through the LDRRMC and Local Development (LDC) to the COA auditor of the LGU;

c.	Municipal Treasurer to transfer immediately the cash corresponding to the unexpended balance as of year-end of LDRRMF for QRF and MOOE from General Fund to Trust Fund.

We further recommended that Management should comply with Section 21 of RA 10121 in the allocation of the required minimum amount to be set aside for LDRRM Fund in order to have sufficient fund in carrying out its disaster risk reduction and management programs, projects, activities, and attain the objective of the law.

